description:
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest acute Trusts in the UK – and with more than 20,000 employees – Manchester University NHS Foundation Trust (MFT) is on an exciting mission to deliver high-quality care to the people of Manchester, Trafford and beyond. Our vision is to create and deliver a seamless 24/7 service that extends beyond excellent care within our nine hospitals and community services within our Local Care Organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support on the separation, transition and integration of Soft FM and Phase recruitment and support the hospital redevelopment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the Deputy Director of Facilities in shaping the future provision of Facilities Services within the Trust. This will include the strategic development of services to ensure they are high quality, progressive, responsive to internal and external demand, patient focused and fully support the strategic and future operational needs of the service delivery contracts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be accountable for all day to day operational aspects of Facilities Services delivered at North Manchester General Hospital); its partnership organisations and internal customers. This will include the support and development of services to ensure they are progressive, responsive to internal and external demand, are patient focused, safe, efficient and effective. The post-holder is required to work within a robust governance structure and performance against agreed service standards and key performance indicators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Soft FM Estates and Facilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Car Parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Catering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning and Domestic Services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Front of House&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Laundry &amp; Linen&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Security&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Telecommunications and Switchboard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transport&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Waste Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and Implementation of Governance and Assurance Framework for Soft FM which must be compliant with the Premises Assurance Model, demonstrate compliance with statutory requirements and Risk Management / Business Continuity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ERIC Data / PLACE / Lord Carter Assessment and External Performance Reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
